        "cooked": "<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/3/4/34e14695b42b3488da0544b1c19438d998bf74a2.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/34e14695b42b3488da0544b1c19438d998bf74a2\" title=\"Screenshot_20260101-231632.Signal\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/4/34e14695b42b3488da0544b1c19438d998bf74a2_2_224x500.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20260101-231632.Signal\" data-base62-sha1=\"7xNtJ5rDRnKMTvY4854103hwr8m\" width=\"224\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/4/34e14695b42b3488da0544b1c19438d998bf74a2_2_224x500.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/4/34e14695b42b3488da0544b1c19438d998bf74a2_2_336x750.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/4/34e14695b42b3488da0544b1c19438d998bf74a2_2_448x1000.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"202023\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot_20260101-231632.Signal</span><span class=\"informations\">1220×2712 161 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>On most folders I see the total amount of chats in it. That could be useful. But in my case on ‘all chats’ It does not tell me how many chat there are, even though that is the most useful thing to know, I could compare with that. Instead it shows a count of chat types. What is the practical use of knowing how many types of chat are in a folder? And do you know anyone who can tell you what chat types are without making a guess? (1-on-1 or group) I Does unread chats count as a different type than read chats? Is notes to self a 1-on1 chat? (currently yes) Is a group I use to part notes with only me as a member a groupchat? (currently yes) See how this can get confusing?</p>\n<p>So, ditch any mention of chat types, and just show the count of chats, counting all types.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, name the types and provide a count for each type</p>\n<p>“</p>\n<p>all chats</p>\n<p>2 groups, 6 private chats, 1 notes to self</p>\n<p>”</p>",
