        "cooked": "<p>after doing some testing, i figured out why this happens - this is not only the case for “all chats” nor even for all suggested chats, but rather for all chats you create that include some kind of chat type. so if you create a folder that includes all 1:1 chats excluding some people, it’d say “one chat type included, 1 chat excluded”.<br>\nthis makes sense, since by including a chat type rather than individual chats, the number of chats will be very high, since it may include people you no longer chat with, groups you’ve left etc.</p>",
